snippet: Doubts about the credibility of the electoral process were sown by the commission’s actions, which included shutting out the former spy chief for falling 31 signatures short in his election paperwork.
abstract: Egypt's election commission disqualifies three presidential candidates, including Hosni Mubarak's former spy chief Omar Suleiman; Suleiman fell just 31 short of the 30,000 notarized statements of endorsements required to enter the race, leaving many Egyptians questioning the credibility of the electoral process.

byline.contributor: Mayy El Sheikh and Omnia Desoukie contributed reporting.

lead_paragraph: Doubts about the credibility of the electoral process were sown by the commission’s actions, which included shutting out the former spy chief for falling 31 signatures short in his election paperwork.

headline.seo: Tumult in Egypt After Panel Bars Presidential Candidates
headline.main: New Tumult in Egypt’s Politics After Panel Bars 3 Candidates for President
headline.print_headline: New Tumult in Egypt’s Politics After Panel Bars 3 Candidates for President
